1
00:04:01,540 --> 00:04:03,212
No Entry

2
00:04:37,740 --> 00:04:40,334
The fruit of Original Sin

3
00:04:58,580 --> 00:05:03,131
Away with it!
- Don't be difficult!

4
00:05:03,580 --> 00:05:06,697
Let's take
our lovely children on an outing!

5
00:05:17,580 --> 00:05:20,538
You can't do this. I know my rights.

6
00:05:20,980 --> 00:05:23,335
I have the authority
to close you down.

7
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:27,455
This exhibit degrades those who see it
and the poor creature himself.

8
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:31,336
He is a freak. How else will he live?

9
00:05:31,820 --> 00:05:34,175
This is entirely different!

10
00:05:34,620 --> 00:05:37,418
This is montrous
and should not be allowed!

11
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:42,411
These officers will see
that you are on your way. Good day!

12
00:05:43,580 --> 00:05:46,014
Move along please!

13
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:52,010
Hold it there, sir. Come this way.

14
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:05,615
On the move again...

15
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:11,812
My treasure.

16
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:52,538
We're seeing a lot more
of these machine accidents.

17
00:06:56,620 --> 00:07:00,772
Abominable things these machines.
You can't reason with them.

18
00:07:01,740 --> 00:07:03,014
What a mess.

19
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,816
Pull on the rope!

20
00:07:10,820 --> 00:07:12,776
Irons, please!

21
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,374
Who is it?

22
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:31,732
Excuse me, sir.
- Yes, what is it?

23
00:07:32,260 --> 00:07:35,536
I found it.
- Good. Did you see it?

24
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:39,140
No.
- Alright.

25
00:07:39,580 --> 00:07:41,855
I'll see you in a moment. Thank you.

26
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:47,498
Who's that?
- A friend of mine.

27
00:07:48,740 --> 00:07:49,695
Oh yes?

28
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:52,938
What are you up to?
- Nothing.

29
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:54,495
Oh, come on!

30
00:07:56,780 --> 00:07:58,771
Nothing of any importance.

31
00:08:50,580 --> 00:08:52,218
Where's Green Street, please?

32
00:08:52,660 --> 00:08:57,211
Second on the left, then right.
- Thanks.

33
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:16,574
Are you the proprietor?
- And who might you be, sir?

34
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:20,410
Just one of the curious.
I'd like to see it.

35
00:10:22,660 --> 00:10:25,015
I don't think so, we're...

36
00:10:27,340 --> 00:10:32,209
closed!
- I'd pay handsomely for a showing.

37
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:35,458
Are you the proprietor?
- Handsomely?. Who sent you?

38
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:38,016
I beg your pardon?
- Never mind.

39
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:44,738
I'm the owner.

40
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:04,009
Life...

41
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:09,815
is full of surprises.

42
00:12:13,620 --> 00:12:16,180
Consider the fate

43
00:12:16,620 --> 00:12:19,009
of this creature's poor mother,

44
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:22,618
struck down...

45
00:12:23,660 --> 00:12:29,895
in the fourth month
of her condition by wild elephants.

46
00:12:30,540 --> 00:12:32,770
Struck down...

47
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:37,372
on an uncharted African isle.

48
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:40,012
The result...

49
00:12:41,740 --> 00:12:44,015
is plain to see.

50
00:12:45,740 --> 00:12:47,810
Ladies and Gentlemen,

51
00:12:49,380 --> 00:12:51,018
the terrible...

52
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:56,052
Elephant Man!

53
00:13:10,220 --> 00:13:12,017
Stand up!
- Stand up!

54
00:13:18,460 --> 00:13:21,816
Turn around!
- Turn around!

55
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:07,018
You'll bring him to me
tomorrow, ten o'clock, Mr....?

56
00:14:07,460 --> 00:14:10,020
Bytes. He'll be there.

57
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:19,817
Here is my card. I'll send a cab.

58
00:14:20,260 --> 00:14:22,820
We have a deal.

59
00:14:24,460 --> 00:14:27,611
We understand each other,

60
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:31,014
more than money has changed hands.

61
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:34,578
We understand each other
completely, my friend.

62
00:14:35,020 --> 00:14:37,409
Yes. Thank you, Mr. Bytes.

63
00:15:15,220 --> 00:15:17,529
Cor, what a stink!

64
00:15:18,460 --> 00:15:20,815
I'm looking for Mr. Frederick Treves.

65
00:15:21,260 --> 00:15:22,818
Please, ma'am.

66
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:27,614
I'll send for him. Nurse!

67
00:15:28,140 --> 00:15:30,859
Mr. Treves, this...

68
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,416
Yes.
- Says, that...

69
00:15:33,860 --> 00:15:35,816
Yes, I was expecting him.

70
00:15:37,060 --> 00:15:40,132
Are you the cab driver? - Yes.
- Anyone else with you?

71
00:15:40,580 --> 00:15:44,971
No, just this gentleman.
- Thank you for your troubles.

72
00:15:45,580 --> 00:15:48,538
Not at all. My pleasure.
- Thank you.

73
00:15:50,580 --> 00:15:51,933
This way, please?

74
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:57,969
I'll be in my room
and I'm not to be disturbed.

75
00:15:58,420 --> 00:16:00,376
Of course, sir.

76
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:05,056
Will you come with me?

77
00:16:08,020 --> 00:16:09,738
You heard the doctor?

78
00:16:14,980 --> 00:16:16,971
Go on!

79
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:58,857
My name is Frederick Treves and I'm
the surgeon at the London Hospital.

80
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:00,255
And...

81
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:06,010
I lecture in anatomy
at the medical college.

82
00:17:07,620 --> 00:17:08,814
Sorry.

83
00:17:10,420 --> 00:17:12,934
I'd like very much to examine you.

84
00:17:16,020 --> 00:17:18,011
Would that be alright?

85
00:17:19,340 --> 00:17:20,819
Please.

86
00:17:25,420 --> 00:17:27,536
I'd like to ask you a few questions.

87
00:17:28,660 --> 00:17:30,855
Would that be alright?

88
00:17:32,460 --> 00:17:36,009
Your owner...The man,
who looks after you, tells me that...

89
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:40,015
you're English
and that your name is John Merrick.

90
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:43,416
John Merrick, is that right?

91
00:17:47,780 --> 00:17:50,817
I tell you what,
I think I'll ask you a question

92
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:55,575
and you shake you head for 'no'.

93
00:17:58,460 --> 00:18:00,098
Have you always been this way?

94
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:03,856
Are you in any pain?

95
00:18:06,740 --> 00:18:08,890
Are your parents still alive?

96
00:18:09,580 --> 00:18:14,529
Do you understand me? Your father,
your mother, are they dead?

97
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:17,693
Freddie, what are you doing...?

98
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:21,416
Oh, I'm sorry. I had no idea...

99
00:18:24,580 --> 00:18:27,811
What have you got there?
- You'll find out at the meeting.

100
00:18:28,260 --> 00:18:30,694
Until then, not a word to anyone.

101
00:18:31,140 --> 00:18:33,938
Alright.
You must have quite a find in there.

102
00:18:34,380 --> 00:18:38,009
I don't know.
- "Nothing of any importance", eh?

103
00:18:38,980 --> 00:18:42,052
Not a word, please, Fox.

104
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:46,893
Alright.

105
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:37,619
I think I'll examine you now.

106
00:19:38,060 --> 00:19:41,609
I'll leave the questions till later.

107
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:46,219
Will you take your hat off?

108
00:19:47,820 --> 00:19:51,290
Don't be frightened.
I simply want to look at you.

109
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:56,177
Take your hat off.
Don't be frightened.

110
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:09,819
Thank you. Good afternoon.

111
00:20:11,020 --> 00:20:13,011
Mr. Thomas, Mr. Rogers!

112
00:20:18,940 --> 00:20:21,010
Pull the curtains aside!

113
00:20:28,260 --> 00:20:32,014
He's English. He is 21 years of age.

114
00:20:33,220 --> 00:20:35,211
His name is John Merrick.

115
00:20:37,020 --> 00:20:39,659
In the course
of my profession I have come upon

116
00:20:40,100 --> 00:20:43,695
many deformities of the face
due to injury or disease

117
00:20:44,140 --> 00:20:48,577
as well as mutilations and contortions
of the body from like causes.

118
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:53,571
I have never seen such a perverted,
degraded version of a human being.

119
00:20:54,020 --> 00:20:57,490
I wish to draw your attention to
his insidious conditions.

120
00:20:57,940 --> 00:20:59,498
Can you see over there?

121
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:03,451
Note, if you will,
the extreme enlargement of the skull

122
00:21:04,180 --> 00:21:06,569
and the limb, which is useless,

123
00:21:07,020 --> 00:21:10,535
the alarming curvature of the spine.
Would you turn round, please?

124
00:21:10,980 --> 00:21:12,413
Turn round, please!

125
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:17,013
The looseness of the skin

126
00:21:17,460 --> 00:21:21,738
and the fibrous tumours
that cover 90% of the body.

127
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:26,130
There is every indication that these
afflictions have existed and have

128
00:21:26,580 --> 00:21:29,219
progressed rapidly since birth.

129
00:21:29,660 --> 00:21:31,776
He suffers from chronic bronchitis.

130
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:35,735
Interesting side note:
Despite these anomalies

131
00:21:36,180 --> 00:21:40,776
the patient's genitals
remain entirely intact and unaffected.

132
00:21:41,220 --> 00:21:43,017
Thank you.

133
00:21:45,580 --> 00:21:48,538
And his left arm
is perfectly normal, as you see.

134
00:21:50,900 --> 00:21:51,810
So gentlemen,

135
00:21:52,260 --> 00:21:55,218
owing to the
congenital extostoses of the skull,

136
00:21:55,660 --> 00:21:58,970
extensive papillomatous growths,
pendulous masses of skin,

137
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:02,298
the enlargement of
the right limb and all the bones,

138
00:22:02,740 --> 00:22:05,459
the distortion of the head
and the extensive area

139
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:08,414
covered by papillomatous growth,

140
00:22:08,860 --> 00:22:12,216
The patient
has been called the "Elephant Man".

141
00:22:12,860 --> 00:22:14,009
Thank you.

142
00:22:40,580 --> 00:22:43,413
You haven't
mentioned his mental state.

143
00:22:43,860 --> 00:22:47,819
He's an imbecile, probably from birth.
A complete idiot.

144
00:22:50,220 --> 00:22:51,539
Pray to God he is.

145
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:03,978
Where have you been?

146
00:23:33,220 --> 00:23:34,209
Out!

147
00:23:36,420 --> 00:23:38,809
How can I eat with a noise like that?

148
00:23:48,420 --> 00:23:49,899
Bytes, don't!

149
00:23:51,860 --> 00:23:54,613
Where were you? What did you do?

150
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:02,329
Our man is sick. Come right away!
- What is it?

151
00:24:02,780 --> 00:24:04,008
Like this...

152
00:24:06,660 --> 00:24:10,335
What did you do with him?
He's been like this all night!

153
00:24:11,860 --> 00:24:14,772
He was fine when he left here.
Now look at him!

154
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:17,017
Yes, I intend to.

155
00:24:18,460 --> 00:24:22,055
What happened?
- He had a fall. He falls.

156
00:24:31,420 --> 00:24:33,376
Looks like a very severe fall.

157
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:36,014
He's a...

158
00:24:36,660 --> 00:24:37,888
... clumsy soul.

159
00:24:38,340 --> 00:24:41,491
Never looks where he's going.
But that's alright.

160
00:24:41,940 --> 00:24:44,010
He has me to take care of him.

161
00:24:44,620 --> 00:24:47,259
Why is he sitting up? He needs rest!

162
00:24:48,380 --> 00:24:50,098
That's how he sleeps.

163
00:24:50,540 --> 00:24:53,657
If he lies down, he'll kill himself.

164
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:57,172
His head's too big.

165
00:24:57,620 --> 00:24:59,975
This man belongs in the hospital.

166
00:25:02,140 --> 00:25:06,179
Can't you treat him here?
Listen, he's my livelihood.

167
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:09,612
We're business partners, he and l.

168
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:15,932
He's the greatest freak in the world!
- Now, you listen,

169
00:25:16,980 --> 00:25:20,336
you're not going to have a livelihood
if he dies. Go and fetch a cab!

170
00:25:20,780 --> 00:25:24,056
I truly appreciate this, my friend.

171
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:26,092
Listen,

172
00:25:26,540 --> 00:25:28,576
there's much I can do for you.

173
00:25:29,020 --> 00:25:34,413
I move in the proper circles.

174
00:25:34,860 --> 00:25:39,490
In fact, anything at all,
if you take my meaning.

175
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:45,328
Everything will be taken care of.
- Good to do business with you.

176
00:27:26,620 --> 00:27:29,009
Can I have a bowl of oatmeal?

177
00:27:30,620 --> 00:27:35,171
Breakfasting with the patients?
- It's for a patient.

178
00:27:35,620 --> 00:27:37,019
There you are.

179
00:27:38,260 --> 00:27:40,490
Thank you. Good morning.
- Morning.

180
00:27:46,380 --> 00:27:47,859
Come here a moment!

181
00:27:57,580 --> 00:27:59,059
What's that you've got there?

182
00:27:59,900 --> 00:28:03,654
Good Heavens! You haven't acquired
a taste for this stuff?

183
00:28:04,100 --> 00:28:06,773
Yes, it's quite nutricious.
- Possibly.

184
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:10,496
Not quite the diet for
a grown man. Nurse!

185
00:28:11,780 --> 00:28:16,490
Just take this to the patient
in the isolation ward, will you?

186
00:28:18,140 --> 00:28:19,095
Yes, sir.

187
00:28:21,380 --> 00:28:23,814
Don't be frightened.
He won't hurt you.

188
00:28:25,340 --> 00:28:29,174
Won't he indeed. Just a moment!
There's something I want to say.

189
00:28:32,540 --> 00:28:35,498
A hospital's no place for secrecy.

190
00:28:35,940 --> 00:28:39,728
Doctors spiriting hooded figures
around cause comment.

191
00:28:40,180 --> 00:28:43,775
Why wasn't he properly admitted?
Why the isolation ward?

192
00:28:44,220 --> 00:28:48,054
He's not contagious, is he?
- No, he's got chronic bronchitis,

193
00:28:48,500 --> 00:28:51,378
and he's been beaten.
- Why not the General Ward then?

194
00:28:51,820 --> 00:28:55,210
He's seriously deformed.

195
00:28:56,460 --> 00:28:58,178
I fear it could shock the patients.

196
00:28:58,620 --> 00:29:03,978
Deformed, is that it?
ls he ultimately incurable?

197
00:29:04,420 --> 00:29:06,217
Yes, sir.
- But you must be aware,

198
00:29:06,660 --> 00:29:09,891
that this hospital
doesn't accept incurables.

199
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:14,970
I'm aware of that.
But this case is quite exceptional.

200
00:29:35,060 --> 00:29:38,132
I quite appreciate your problem.

201
00:29:38,580 --> 00:29:42,493
Why not contact
the Royal Hospital for lncurables?

202
00:29:42,940 --> 00:29:47,172
Perhaps they might find him a place.
- Yes. Would you like to meet him?

203
00:30:03,740 --> 00:30:04,695
Excuse me!

204
00:30:06,420 --> 00:30:07,819
The Elephant Man.

205
00:30:13,980 --> 00:30:15,254
Sorry.

206
00:30:16,340 --> 00:30:17,614
Sorry.

207
00:30:21,780 --> 00:30:24,010
I should have warned you.

208
00:30:24,980 --> 00:30:27,892
Please forgive me. You alright?

209
00:30:31,460 --> 00:30:33,769
Please send Mrs. Mothershead up here.

210
00:30:34,220 --> 00:30:37,496
Tell her to knock and wait for me.

211
00:30:48,300 --> 00:30:50,609
I'm sorry about that.

212
00:30:52,820 --> 00:30:56,256
We'll bring you another breakfast.
You must be very hungry.

213
00:30:58,180 --> 00:31:02,537
You'll be comfortable here.
I'll see you get everything you need.

214
00:34:16,540 --> 00:34:17,655
Blimey!

215
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:26,656
So, this is the Elephant Man.

216
00:34:27,980 --> 00:34:30,892
I ain't seen nothing like you before.

217
00:34:32,420 --> 00:34:34,809
What the hell happened to you?

218
00:34:39,380 --> 00:34:40,893
Dumb, eh?

219
00:34:42,460 --> 00:34:45,020
I like people that can keep quiet.

220
00:34:48,340 --> 00:34:50,410
Here, have a drink!

221
00:34:53,740 --> 00:34:56,015
Go on! No?

222
00:35:00,460 --> 00:35:02,815
You should be more sociable.

223
00:35:04,780 --> 00:35:06,179
Get yourself disliked.

224
00:35:12,220 --> 00:35:17,294
We're going to be good friends and my
friends will want to meet you.

225
00:35:17,740 --> 00:35:21,938
And they will, believe me.

226
00:35:33,580 --> 00:35:36,048
I've brought your breakfast.
What are you doing down there?

227
00:35:36,660 --> 00:35:38,616
Come up on the bed.

228
00:35:39,060 --> 00:35:40,095
Come on!

229
00:36:14,300 --> 00:36:17,531
All he understands is a good smack.
- He's had his share of smacks.

230
00:36:17,980 --> 00:36:22,496
That drives him under the bed.
Treat him with kindness and patience.

231
00:36:22,940 --> 00:36:27,297
Perhaps you've
got time for that sort of treatment.

232
00:36:27,740 --> 00:36:31,574
I've got a hospital to run.
Don't you waste your time, with him.

233
00:36:32,780 --> 00:36:35,738
It's like talking to a brick wall.

234
00:36:36,180 --> 00:36:38,819
I don't mean to be harsh,

235
00:36:40,700 --> 00:36:42,930
but he doesn't belong here.

236
00:36:44,300 --> 00:36:49,215
Honestly, sir,
what can you do for him?

237
00:37:01,580 --> 00:37:04,253
By the way, Mr. Carr-Gomm said

238
00:37:04,700 --> 00:37:07,089
he'd like to see you
when you can spare a moment.

239
00:37:07,540 --> 00:37:08,609
Yes.
- Thank you.

240
00:37:14,820 --> 00:37:17,493
I can't help you, unless you help me.

241
00:37:25,820 --> 00:37:29,017
I believe there's something
you want to say to me.

242
00:37:29,460 --> 00:37:31,655
Something back there.

243
00:37:32,100 --> 00:37:35,012
I can't help you, unless you help me!

244
00:37:37,700 --> 00:37:40,658
I believe you want to say something.

245
00:37:41,820 --> 00:37:45,017
I've got to understand
what you're feeling and thinking.

246
00:37:47,020 --> 00:37:48,612
Do you understand me?

247
00:37:51,860 --> 00:37:55,011
Just nod your head.
Can you understand me?

248
00:37:55,620 --> 00:37:58,009
Nod your head if you understand me.

249
00:38:02,580 --> 00:38:04,013
Alright.

250
00:38:06,020 --> 00:38:07,897
You do understand.

251
00:38:08,340 --> 00:38:12,299
I want to hear you talk.
You are not a wall.

252
00:38:12,740 --> 00:38:15,937
Do you understand?
I want you to talk to me.

253
00:38:16,380 --> 00:38:18,814
Now. I want to hear you say it.

254
00:38:20,220 --> 00:38:24,930
I want to hear how you say things.
I'm not going to hurt you.

255
00:38:25,380 --> 00:38:26,608
Got to hear!

256
00:38:27,060 --> 00:38:31,019
Very slowly, I want you to say "yes".

257
00:38:32,420 --> 00:38:33,535
Say "yes".

258
00:38:38,300 --> 00:38:39,255
Yes.

