519
01:03:14,180 --> 01:03:17,013
No. It's a cathedral.

520
01:03:17,540 --> 01:03:18,495
Do you see?

521
01:03:20,460 --> 01:03:24,612
I have to rely on my imagination,

522
01:03:25,060 --> 01:03:28,894
for what I can't actually see.

523
01:03:38,820 --> 01:03:43,416
Mr. Treves tells me
you're in the theatre.

524
01:03:43,860 --> 01:03:48,376
Do you live there?
- Oh no, I just work there.

525
01:03:48,820 --> 01:03:54,770
It must be wonderful to work there.

526
01:03:55,220 --> 01:03:58,257
Is it beautiful?
- You've never been?

527
01:03:59,140 --> 01:04:00,812
I'm afraid not.

528
01:04:01,380 --> 01:04:05,134
You must go! The theatre is
the most beautiful place on earth!

529
01:04:05,580 --> 01:04:08,413
Of course I am a bit partial.

530
01:04:08,860 --> 01:04:12,011
The theatre is romance.

531
01:04:14,100 --> 01:04:15,055
Romance?

532
01:04:17,140 --> 01:04:18,095
Oh yes...

533
01:04:20,140 --> 01:04:23,018
I've brought you something else!

534
01:04:28,740 --> 01:04:31,812
Thank you.
- Have you read it?

535
01:04:32,260 --> 01:04:35,491
No, but I certainly shall.

536
01:04:44,740 --> 01:04:47,254
"Romeo and Juliet"!

537
01:04:47,700 --> 01:04:50,009
Yes, I've heard of this.

538
01:04:53,580 --> 01:04:57,892
"If I profane with my unworthiest hand

539
01:04:58,340 --> 01:05:03,414
this holy shrine,
the gentle fine is this:

540
01:05:03,860 --> 01:05:09,218
Thy lips, two blushing pilgrims,

541
01:05:09,660 --> 01:05:17,294
ready stand, to smooth that
rough touch with a tender kiss."

542
01:05:18,980 --> 01:05:22,290
"Good Pilgrim,
you do wrong your hand too much,

543
01:05:22,740 --> 01:05:24,731
which mannerly devotion show in this.

544
01:05:25,180 --> 01:05:28,809
For saints have hands
that pilgrims' hands do touch.

545
01:05:29,260 --> 01:05:31,410
And palm to palm's
holy Palmer's kiss."

546
01:05:33,140 --> 01:05:38,772
"Oh then, dear Saint,
let lips do what hands do.

547
01:05:39,220 --> 01:05:45,693
They pray, grant thou
lest faith turn to despair."

548
01:05:46,140 --> 01:05:51,294
"Saints do not move,
though grant for prayer's sake."

549
01:05:52,740 --> 01:05:59,373
"Then move not,
while my prayer's effect I take.

550
01:05:59,820 --> 01:06:05,338
Thus from my lips,
by thine, my sin is purged."

551
01:06:10,180 --> 01:06:12,250
And then it says: they kiss.

552
01:06:15,500 --> 01:06:18,776
"Then have my lips
the sin that they have took."

553
01:06:24,140 --> 01:06:26,938
"Sin from my lips?

554
01:06:27,380 --> 01:06:30,929
O trespass, sweetly urg'd.

555
01:06:31,380 --> 01:06:34,850
Give me my sin again."

556
01:06:39,860 --> 01:06:44,058
You're not an Elephant Man at all.

557
01:06:46,660 --> 01:06:47,536
No?

558
01:06:48,100 --> 01:06:51,615
No. You're Romeo.

559
01:06:59,780 --> 01:07:02,010
"Mrs. Kendal,
always at the forefront of fashion,

560
01:07:02,460 --> 01:07:05,099
was seen leaving
"The London" the other afternoon.

561
01:07:05,540 --> 01:07:09,135
No, dear readers,
the actress has not been taken ill,

562
01:07:09,580 --> 01:07:14,859
but said she was visiting a friend.
Who was the lucky recipient?

563
01:07:15,300 --> 01:07:19,259
Enquiries proved it to be none other
than John Merrick, the Elephant Man,

564
01:07:19,700 --> 01:07:22,453
with whom our readers are familiar.

565
01:07:22,900 --> 01:07:28,930
After a chat of 45 minutes, she left
him with an autographed portrait."

566
01:07:29,380 --> 01:07:31,132
I saw it in his room.

567
01:07:31,580 --> 01:07:34,652
"Owing to a disfigurement
of the most extreme nature,

568
01:07:35,100 --> 01:07:38,775
Mr. Merrick has never been
presented to London society.

569
01:07:39,220 --> 01:07:43,498
But knowing that wherever Mrs. Kendal
goes, other inevitably follow,

570
01:07:43,940 --> 01:07:47,979
the question arises - will London
society present itself to him?"

571
01:07:48,420 --> 01:07:51,890
This walking stick is so dashing!

572
01:07:52,340 --> 01:07:56,015
And more elegant than my old one!

573
01:07:58,140 --> 01:08:00,051
More tea?

574
01:08:06,540 --> 01:08:09,691
I don't go out
as often as I would like,

575
01:08:10,140 --> 01:08:15,260
because naturally people find
my appearance disturbing.

576
01:08:15,700 --> 01:08:18,009
If you have a chill
I could close the window.

577
01:08:18,460 --> 01:08:21,338
No, I'm fine, please...

578
01:08:21,780 --> 01:08:22,735
Thank you.

579
01:08:24,460 --> 01:08:25,415
Thank you.

580
01:08:26,980 --> 01:08:28,299
You see,

581
01:08:29,780 --> 01:08:34,808
people are frightened
by what they don't understand.

582
01:08:35,620 --> 01:08:41,855
And it is hard to understand,
even for me because my mother

583
01:08:43,220 --> 01:08:45,688
was so very beautiful!

584
01:08:55,220 --> 01:08:57,939
No more visitors today.

585
01:08:58,380 --> 01:09:01,452
I've got a lecture. Till this evening!
- Excuse me, sir,

586
01:09:01,900 --> 01:09:05,051
I would like a word with you.
- What is it?

587
01:09:05,500 --> 01:09:08,617
I don't quite understand

588
01:09:09,060 --> 01:09:11,938
why you allow people in there.

589
01:09:12,380 --> 01:09:14,575
He enjoys it and it's good for him.

590
01:09:15,020 --> 01:09:19,377
But you saw the expression on their
faces, they didn't hide their disgust!

591
01:09:19,820 --> 01:09:23,369
They don't care about John.
They want to impress their friends.

592
01:09:23,820 --> 01:09:27,290
I think you're being rather harsh.
- I beg your pardon.

593
01:09:27,740 --> 01:09:31,210
You hardly showed him much kindness
when he first arrived, did you?

594
01:09:31,660 --> 01:09:34,970
I bathed him, I fed him
and I cleaned up after him!

595
01:09:35,420 --> 01:09:37,570
And my nurses do the same.

596
01:09:38,020 --> 01:09:44,619
If "kindness" can be called care

597
01:09:45,060 --> 01:09:47,733
then I did show him loving kindness!

598
01:09:48,180 --> 01:09:51,252
I didn't mean it exactly that way.

599
01:09:51,700 --> 01:09:55,295
I appreciate your concern
and everything you've done for him.

600
01:09:55,740 --> 01:09:59,528
But I am the physician
and must do what's best for him.

601
01:09:59,980 --> 01:10:03,211
Please now, I'm very late.
- If you ask my opinion,

602
01:10:03,660 --> 01:10:08,609
he's only being stared at again!
- Thank you.

603
01:10:34,020 --> 01:10:36,011
Night time!

604
01:13:16,380 --> 01:13:17,335
Freddie!

605
01:13:19,460 --> 01:13:21,018
What's the matter?

606
01:13:25,420 --> 01:13:28,571
I've been thinking about Mr. Bytes.
- Why on earth?

607
01:13:29,020 --> 01:13:33,013
I believe Mr. Bytes and I
are very much alike.

608
01:13:33,660 --> 01:13:35,013
That's absurd!

609
01:13:38,020 --> 01:13:40,614
It seems I've

610
01:13:41,140 --> 01:13:44,337
made Mr. Merrick
into a curiosity again,

611
01:13:44,780 --> 01:13:48,216
only this time in a hospital
rather than a carnival.

612
01:13:50,580 --> 01:13:53,413
My name is constantly in the
newpapers and I'm always being

613
01:13:53,860 --> 01:13:58,695
praised to the skies. Patients
ask expressly for my services.

614
01:13:59,140 --> 01:14:01,096
Because you are a fine doctor.

615
01:14:01,540 --> 01:14:05,738
John Merrick is happier and more
fulfilled then ever

616
01:14:06,180 --> 01:14:09,013
and it's completely due to you.

617
01:14:09,740 --> 01:14:13,574
What was it all for? Why did I do it?

618
01:14:14,100 --> 01:14:16,614
What are you trying to say?

619
01:14:20,300 --> 01:14:22,814
Am I a good man

620
01:14:23,260 --> 01:14:25,649
or am I a bad man?

621
01:14:29,937 --> 01:14:32,815
Steady on, Treves. Steady on.

622
01:14:33,497 --> 01:14:35,567
Please sit down, won't you?

623
01:14:40,897 --> 01:14:45,607
We usually open the proceedings
by reading the minutes.

624
01:14:46,057 --> 01:14:49,891
In the interests of urgency
I think we should conclude the matter

625
01:14:50,337 --> 01:14:54,694
under discussion, the case of
John Merrick, the Elephant Man.

626
01:14:55,137 --> 01:14:57,890
One moment, Mr. Chairman!

627
01:14:58,337 --> 01:15:02,296
As far as I'm concerned, this
creature has no business here.

628
01:15:03,337 --> 01:15:07,808
I for one am sick and tired
of this freak-hunting

629
01:15:08,257 --> 01:15:12,648
by ambitious young doctors,
trying to make name's for themselves.

630
01:15:13,097 --> 01:15:16,373
To parade them about
in front of the society is one thing,

631
01:15:16,817 --> 01:15:20,492
but to waste the committee's time
with requests for shelter

632
01:15:20,937 --> 01:15:24,213
for these abominations of nature
is quite another.

633
01:15:28,257 --> 01:15:30,612
You must be more careful!

634
01:15:31,137 --> 01:15:34,095
In the light
of these facts, our course is clear:

635
01:15:34,537 --> 01:15:38,530
The question is not whether to
accept this creature as a patient, but

636
01:15:38,977 --> 01:15:43,289
when will the rooms be vacated
for the use of more deserving cases?

637
01:15:44,457 --> 01:15:48,166
I move that this Elephant Man be
removed from the premises immediately.

638
01:15:48,617 --> 01:15:51,814
We have
a sacred duty to cure the sick

639
01:15:52,257 --> 01:15:56,648
not to care for circus animals!
That is my last word on the subject.

640
01:15:57,097 --> 01:16:01,534
Shall we vote?
- You are unshakeable in this?

641
01:16:01,977 --> 01:16:04,537
Mr. Chairman, do you not have ears?

642
01:16:04,977 --> 01:16:07,411
I am unalterably opposed!

643
01:16:08,177 --> 01:16:10,054
My mind is made up.

644
01:16:11,817 --> 01:16:14,889
You shall not sway me.
May we now vote,

645
01:16:15,337 --> 01:16:17,612
at long last?

646
01:16:18,737 --> 01:16:19,772
Yes, Broadneck.

647
01:16:20,217 --> 01:16:22,606
I think the time has come.

648
01:16:23,057 --> 01:16:25,776
Gentlemen, Her Royal Highness

649
01:16:26,217 --> 01:16:29,289
Alexandra, Princess of Wales.

650
01:16:46,417 --> 01:16:48,772
Good morning.
I hope I'm not disturbing you.

651
01:16:49,217 --> 01:16:53,335
Your presence here
is always greatly appreciated.

652
01:16:53,777 --> 01:16:57,326
We were just taking a vote
on Mr. Merrick.

653
01:17:00,537 --> 01:17:04,007
Her Royal Highness has shown
great interest in Mr. Merrick's fate.

654
01:17:04,457 --> 01:17:06,493
I have, sir, as has the Queen.

655
01:17:09,817 --> 01:17:14,766
I have a communication from the
Queen, which I should read to you.

656
01:17:17,857 --> 01:17:20,769
"To the Governing Committee,
London Hospital.

657
01:17:28,137 --> 01:17:30,605
I would like to commend you

658
01:17:31,057 --> 01:17:34,766
for the charitable face
you have shown Mr. John Merrick.

659
01:17:35,217 --> 01:17:39,688
It is laudable that you have
provided one of England's

660
01:17:40,137 --> 01:17:44,210
unfortunate sons with a safe
and tranquil harbour, a home.

661
01:17:44,657 --> 01:17:48,445
For this immeasurable kindness,
as well as the many acts of mercy

662
01:17:48,897 --> 01:17:51,775
on behalf of the poor,
of which Mr. Carr-Gomm

663
01:17:52,217 --> 01:17:54,367
has kept me informed,

664
01:17:54,817 --> 01:17:59,208
I gratefully thank you.
Signed, Victoria."

665
01:18:04,057 --> 01:18:07,936
I am sure I can count on you
gentlemen to do the Christian thing.

666
01:18:08,377 --> 01:18:12,006
Thank you very much.
I'm sure we shall all try.

667
01:18:13,017 --> 01:18:17,647
I move that Mr. John Merrick
be admitted on a permanent basis

668
01:18:18,097 --> 01:18:23,808
provided the hospital receives
a yearly sum for the cost of one bed.

669
01:18:24,457 --> 01:18:26,652
All those in favour?

670
01:18:37,777 --> 01:18:40,735
Thank you, gentlemen.
The motion is carried.

671
01:18:46,257 --> 01:18:48,407
Yes, come in!

672
01:18:54,137 --> 01:18:59,006
Good afternoon. Mr. Carr-Gomm
has something he wants to say to you.

673
01:19:00,017 --> 01:19:01,973
Mr. Merrick, I am very pleased

674
01:19:02,417 --> 01:19:06,410
in being able to welcome you
officially to the London Hospital.

675
01:19:06,857 --> 01:19:11,214
The Governing Committee has
unanimously voted that you should be

676
01:19:11,657 --> 01:19:15,286
provided with these rooms on a
permanent basis. This is your home.

677
01:19:15,737 --> 01:19:20,288
I'm so very very glad for you.
- Welcome home, lad!

678
01:19:24,337 --> 01:19:25,816
This is...

679
01:19:27,777 --> 01:19:30,007
my home?
- Yes.

680
01:19:30,457 --> 01:19:34,530
Please will you thank
the committee for me?

681
01:19:34,977 --> 01:19:39,653
I will do my utmost
to merit their kindness.

682
01:19:40,097 --> 01:19:44,488
This... is my home?

683
01:19:45,737 --> 01:19:48,012
Yes. And this is for you.

684
01:19:54,737 --> 01:19:56,011
Your dressing case!

685
01:20:05,417 --> 01:20:07,009
Oh, thank you!

686
01:20:07,897 --> 01:20:10,013
Thank you!

687
01:20:12,697 --> 01:20:14,176
Oh my friends, thank you!

688
01:20:14,617 --> 01:20:16,016
Thank you!

689
01:20:18,057 --> 01:20:19,888
My friends!

690
01:20:25,217 --> 01:20:26,696
Oh my friends!

691
01:20:27,137 --> 01:20:29,093
Oh my friends!

692
01:20:29,537 --> 01:20:31,573
Thank you!

693
01:20:55,257 --> 01:20:57,817
Who's next?
- I say!

694
01:20:59,257 --> 01:21:01,248
What you again?
- Well...

695
01:21:01,697 --> 01:21:04,006
These young ladies have never seen it.

696
01:21:07,937 --> 01:21:09,495
You're on, mate!

697
01:21:12,137 --> 01:21:14,412
That's it for this performance!

698
01:21:15,337 --> 01:21:18,249
Jim, can I go?
- Sit down, Charlie!

699
01:21:18,697 --> 01:21:21,006
There's always tomorrow, don't worry.

700
01:21:25,137 --> 01:21:27,287
Room for one more?

701
01:21:27,737 --> 01:21:30,012
At the right price.

702
01:21:31,897 --> 01:21:32,932
There's room.

703
01:21:44,257 --> 01:21:46,896
Keep the noise down!

704
01:21:49,097 --> 01:21:52,294
We don't want to frighten him!

705
01:22:24,177 --> 01:22:29,297
My name is John Merrick.

706
01:22:30,497 --> 01:22:35,696
I'm very, very pleased to meet you.

707
01:22:40,737 --> 01:22:42,011
I think

708
01:22:43,737 --> 01:22:46,615
you are very beautiful!

709
01:22:49,737 --> 01:22:51,807
Curtain time!

710
01:22:52,337 --> 01:22:55,852
You look beautiful, darling!
I wouldn't change a thing!

711
01:22:56,937 --> 01:22:59,610
You look like the Prince of Wales!

712
01:23:01,057 --> 01:23:03,013
Here, my friends!

713
01:23:04,617 --> 01:23:06,130
The Elephant Man!

714
01:23:09,537 --> 01:23:13,655
I told you it was horrible,
just horrible.

715
01:23:22,737 --> 01:23:25,490
Perhaps the ladies
would like a closer look?

716
01:23:25,937 --> 01:23:29,566
Yes, yes!
- No, Jack, please!

717
01:23:30,497 --> 01:23:32,010
Right, in you go!

718
01:23:37,537 --> 01:23:39,812
He's quite a ladies' man!

719
01:23:41,457 --> 01:23:44,176
Give the ladies' man a little kiss!

720
01:23:45,337 --> 01:23:47,453
Go on, give him a kiss!

721
01:23:47,897 --> 01:23:49,728
Jack, leave off!

722
01:23:59,297 --> 01:24:01,492
That's enough romance!

723
01:24:01,937 --> 01:24:03,336
Time for beddy-byes!

724
01:24:51,697 --> 01:24:53,972
Keep the noise down!

725
01:24:54,417 --> 01:24:58,012
Keep it quiet! Now watch this!

726
01:25:41,297 --> 01:25:43,367
Okay, that's enough!

727
01:25:44,417 --> 01:25:47,250
Show's over!
See you back at the Peacock!

728
01:25:50,257 --> 01:25:52,009
Get out of it!

729
01:26:20,257 --> 01:26:21,406
Here, come on.

730
01:26:24,737 --> 01:26:27,376
There you are. That's better.

731
01:26:30,257 --> 01:26:32,327
I've done well tonight.

732
01:26:32,777 --> 01:26:34,005
Here,

733
01:26:34,817 --> 01:26:37,092
buy yourself a sweet!

734
01:27:02,257 --> 01:27:03,485
My treasure!

735
01:28:04,737 --> 01:28:05,692
John?

736
01:28:10,017 --> 01:28:10,972
John!

737
01:28:17,657 --> 01:28:20,888
Mr. Treves,
I know what happened last night.

738
01:28:30,737 --> 01:28:31,692
Oh, God!

739
01:28:50,857 --> 01:28:52,006
Where is he?

740
01:28:52,457 --> 01:28:54,015
Where is Mr. Merrick?

741
01:29:00,057 --> 01:29:02,696
Where is Mr. Merrick?

742
01:29:04,697 --> 01:29:07,495
I don't know what you mean.
- Don't lie to me!

743
01:29:08,857 --> 01:29:11,417
I know all about it, you were seen.

744
01:29:11,857 --> 01:29:16,248
You're involved with Bytes,
aren't you? Where is he?

745
01:29:16,697 --> 01:29:20,770
Wait a minute! I haven't taken him
anywhere. I dunno no Bytes.

746
01:29:21,217 --> 01:29:26,655
We were just having a bit fun.
We never hurt him.

747
01:29:27,097 --> 01:29:29,611
You tortured him! He's gone!

748
01:29:30,057 --> 01:29:32,366
When I left him he was in bed!

749
01:29:35,577 --> 01:29:38,808
You're not listening to me!
I dunno no Bytes!

750
01:29:39,257 --> 01:29:44,251
I've done nothing wrong!
People pay money to see your monster!

751
01:29:44,697 --> 01:29:47,291
You're the monster, the freak.
Get out of here!

752
01:29:47,737 --> 01:29:52,288
Get out!
- You don't frighten me!

753
01:29:53,777 --> 01:29:56,337
I'm glad what I done.
You can do nothing about it!

754
01:29:56,777 --> 01:30:00,008
Only Mothershead can sack me now!

755
01:30:04,537 --> 01:30:05,606
Done!

756
01:30:22,057 --> 01:30:24,093
There's something I'd like to say.

757
01:30:25,177 --> 01:30:28,328
You know I felt
as deeply as you did about John.

758
01:30:28,777 --> 01:30:32,406
Well now he's disappeared,
very likely to the continent.

759
01:30:32,857 --> 01:30:37,533
You can't go after him,
you're needed here by your patients.

760
01:30:37,977 --> 01:30:42,334
You did everything in your power.

761
01:30:42,777 --> 01:30:45,007
Everything in your power.

762
01:32:09,657 --> 01:32:11,010
Get a stool!

763
01:32:37,217 --> 01:32:38,696
Get up, you bastard!

764
01:33:03,257 --> 01:33:07,011
Look at all these beautiful animals!

765
01:33:11,177 --> 01:33:13,816
What a lot you have!

766
01:33:25,297 --> 01:33:27,492
That sly bastard!

767
01:33:32,257 --> 01:33:35,010
He's doing this to spite me!

768
01:33:45,057 --> 01:33:48,606
You're doing this to spite me
and it's got to stop!

769
01:33:49,057 --> 01:33:52,606
Bytes, he's sick!
- Let him die!

770
01:33:55,737 --> 01:33:58,410
But don't think
I'm going to bury that...

771
01:34:00,657 --> 01:34:03,490
bag of flesh. No!

772
01:34:10,657 --> 01:34:12,648
And that's a fact.

773
01:34:19,137 --> 01:34:22,527
Bytes, stop!
- I'm going to fetch that lump of fat!

774
01:34:38,177 --> 01:34:39,132
Stop!

775
01:35:07,137 --> 01:35:08,695
Bytes, stop!

776
01:36:13,857 --> 01:36:16,087
We've decided,

777
01:36:19,097 --> 01:36:22,328
we're going to get you out of here.

778
01:36:47,417 --> 01:36:49,328
Alright?

779
01:38:06,057 --> 01:38:07,410
Luck, my friend!

780
01:38:10,137 --> 01:38:13,607
Luck! And who needs it more than we?

781
01:39:40,057 --> 01:39:43,413
Sir, why is your head so big?

782
01:39:47,417 --> 01:39:49,009
Why is your head so big?

783
01:39:51,897 --> 01:39:55,128
Why is your head so big? Tell me!

784
01:40:00,817 --> 01:40:03,012
Why is your head so big?

785
01:41:23,217 --> 01:41:25,173
No!

786
01:41:26,697 --> 01:41:29,006
I'm not an elephant!

787
01:41:31,537 --> 01:41:34,449
I am not an animal!

788
01:41:37,057 --> 01:41:40,572
I am a human being!

789
01:41:45,417 --> 01:41:50,013
I am a man.

790
01:41:56,937 --> 01:41:59,007
Out of the way, sir. Excuse me!

791
01:42:02,497 --> 01:42:05,295
Mr. Treves, they've found him!

792
01:42:05,657 --> 01:42:08,091
They've found John!

793
01:42:27,577 --> 01:42:29,056
Keep still!

794
01:42:31,617 --> 01:42:34,256
It was nice of Mrs. Kendal
to give me this dress.

795
01:42:34,697 --> 01:42:36,608
It's beautiful!

796
01:42:39,977 --> 01:42:42,127
Does she know John's dying?

797
01:42:44,137 --> 01:42:47,686
Yes, she knows.

798
01:43:02,457 --> 01:43:04,607
How do I look?

799
01:43:05,057 --> 01:43:06,410
Splendid!

800
01:43:06,857 --> 01:43:10,532
You will not look out of place.
You look absolutely splendid!

801
01:43:10,977 --> 01:43:14,014
Splendid... Shall we go?

802
01:43:15,697 --> 01:43:20,691
I can't tell you
how sorry I am for what happened.

803
01:43:21,137 --> 01:43:24,049
You see, I had no idea.

804
01:43:24,497 --> 01:43:26,886
You mustn't blame yourself.

805
01:43:27,337 --> 01:43:30,852
Mr. Treves, don't worry about me.

806
01:43:31,697 --> 01:43:33,255
My friend,

807
01:43:33,697 --> 01:43:37,451
I am happy every hour of the day.

808
01:43:39,017 --> 01:43:43,408
My life is full,
because I know that I am loved.

809
01:43:47,217 --> 01:43:50,095
I have gained myself.

810
01:43:57,577 --> 01:44:02,856
I could not say that,
were it not for you.

811
01:44:07,457 --> 01:44:08,412
Well...

812
01:44:09,457 --> 01:44:13,530
you have done so much for me as well.

813
01:44:14,737 --> 01:44:15,806
Thank you!

814
01:44:20,937 --> 01:44:24,896
I'll fetch Mrs. Mothershead and Nora
and be back in a few minutes!

815
01:44:27,577 --> 01:44:29,568
Very good, my friend.

816
01:44:33,977 --> 01:44:35,410
My friend!

817
01:47:25,017 --> 01:47:26,735
Mrs. Kendal!

818
01:47:31,577 --> 01:47:34,853
Your Royal Highness,
Ladies and Gentlemen!

819
01:47:35,297 --> 01:47:39,813
Tonight's performance was special
for me, as it was to someone else,

820
01:47:40,257 --> 01:47:42,896
a man who knows and loves the theatre.

821
01:47:43,337 --> 01:47:46,170
And yet this
is the first time he's ever been here.

822
01:47:47,777 --> 01:47:51,486
I wish the whole company wishes
with all their hearts

823
01:47:51,937 --> 01:47:55,691
to dedicate tonight's performance
to Mr. John Merrick,

824
01:47:56,137 --> 01:47:58,207
my very dear friend.

825
01:48:09,817 --> 01:48:11,887
Go on, John, they want to see you!

826
01:48:12,337 --> 01:48:16,330
I can't.
- It's alright, stand up!

827
01:48:52,217 --> 01:48:55,607
I really did believe

828
01:48:56,057 --> 01:48:59,493
that the ogre
would never get out of the dungeon.

829
01:49:01,177 --> 01:49:03,486
You really enjoyed yourself.

830
01:49:04,537 --> 01:49:09,008
Oh, it was wonderful!

831
01:49:10,297 --> 01:49:13,050
We really must go again some evening.

832
01:49:13,497 --> 01:49:16,216
Oh, I hope so.

833
01:49:16,657 --> 01:49:18,010
Yes, we will, we will.

834
01:49:20,017 --> 01:49:21,894
Good, I'm pleased.

835
01:49:22,337 --> 01:49:26,967
I ought to go. Must get some sleep.

836
01:49:27,857 --> 01:49:30,007
Good night. Sleep well.

837
01:49:31,937 --> 01:49:34,770
And you too, my friend.

838
01:49:36,057 --> 01:49:39,174
So pleased you enjoyed yourself.
Good night.

839
01:49:43,577 --> 01:49:45,010
Good night.

840
01:51:10,697 --> 01:51:15,407
It's finished!

841
01:54:38,137 --> 01:54:42,016
Never, never! Nothing will die.

842
01:54:42,457 --> 01:54:46,052
The stream flows, the wind blows,

843
01:54:46,497 --> 01:54:50,536
the cloud fleets, the heart beats.

844
01:55:10,937 --> 01:55:12,973
Nothing will die.

